The Quantified Self- My Travel Year

The Quantified Self is a movement that began to extract more information about oneself, especially with the help of wearable technologies to give a deeper insight into ones lifestyle and habits. When I was presented the opportunity to work on the QS methods, I immediately learnt that it would be a great tool to understand my travel habits.

Motivation: Travel is a significant hobby of mine and I am aware that I spend a considerable amount of money on travel. Infact, I often find myself planning my monthly expenses and investments surrounding travel. In addition, the past year, I have travelled mroe than the remainder of my life put together and hence, I am interested in documenting my Travel Year through this project.

Questions:

The questions I have answered through this project are as follows:

  1. What time of the year do I travel spend the most on travel?

  2. What purpose do I spent most of my travel bucks on?

  3. Which time of the year do I travel the most?

  4. Which has been the most travel intensive month of the year for me? Does it correlate with the amount spent on travel during this month?

  5. Most expensive locations travelled in past year.

Data Acquisition

In order to perform this analysis, I have looked at my credit card bills, my spreadsheets used for documenting iterinaries and travel expenses and Splitwise accounts shared with friends.

Methods:

Data mining and manipulation- Upon extracting data from various sources and transferring into excel sheets for analysis, I performed formatting and split the expenses by month, destination, mode, purpose & activity to facilitate analysis.

In order to answer the first question,a bar plot would be the best method.

For question 2, a donut chart would provide the easiest and most effective method of visualisation given the number of categories are few ie. 3.

Questions 3,4 & 5 are best visualized by bar plots faceted by the variable of interest.

Amount of Money Spent on Travel According to Purpose

p<-ggplot(data=data,aes(Purpose,Expenditure))+stat_summary(fun.y=sum,geom="bar")

Visualization 4:

Relationship between number of destinations and amount of money spent

mydata2<-read_excel("/Users/pinkymanoj/Desktop/TravelData2.xlsx")
data2<-data.frame(mydata2)
Spending<-data2$ExpSum
Months<-data2$MonthSum
MilesTravelled<-data2$MilesSum
ggplot(data=data2,aes(x=Months, y=Spending, fill=MilesTravelled))+geom_bar(stat="identity")

In Jul 2017, I travelled most number of miles in any given month & I also spent most amount of money on travel. This was when I went on a Euro Tour for my honeymoon. However, it is not always true that travelling to more places requires more spending or vice-versa as seen from August & September 2017.
